cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving machine translation models using syntax information. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new graph-structured encoder, which involves neural network architecture and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on translation tasks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanism, which is a common technique in neural networks for computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible category. Finally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks, which is a common technique in neural networks for natural language processing, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
